description:
Summer Special!

It's SUMMERTIME! The air is fresh. The birds are chirping. The flowers and blooming. and our little Wolf Boy is feeling....ferocious! WATCH OUT everybody! PATRICK is on summer vacation! And you know with Patrick around, things like fishing, baseball, and lemonade stands have a whole new meaning. HEY! Who took a bite out of this baseball bat? The answer will tickle your funny-bone! Join us for this celebration of Summer Fun! By the Eisner Award winning creators...ART BALTAZAR and FRANCO!

aw yeah ground-floor!
name: Summer Special!

description:
Next Halloween Special

It Next Halloween already! And this time Patrick is ready! Watch out squirrel! Patrick might add you to his treats! Join us for the fun and laughter as Patrick and his friends carry on the tradition that celebrates ghosts and goblins. Guest appearances by the Grimm Reaper, Li'l Neve, and of course, Patrick's parents. Don't let the beg bug go bump in the night! From the Eisner Award winning creators... ART BALTAZAR and FRANCO! Aw Yeah!
name: Next Halloween Special

description:
SUPER-HERO SPECIAL!

AW YEAH! Some arrive from distant planets. Some are created from science experiments gone awry. Some emerge from the mean streets of the city. And some are born from bug bites! YES! I'm talking about Super Heroes! Join us for another Patrick the Wolf Boy adventure as his imagination enters the world of Super Heroes and Comic Books! AW YEAH! Who could his arch nemesis be? Watch out! There's a giant spider in the room! Will it give you super powers? What's up with those Romance Comics? Where's my cape? I'm outta here! Guest starring Li'l Neve, Patrick's Parents, and a few familiar characters wearing capes. AW YEAH HOMAGE! For that super hero lover in you.

by Art Baltazar and Franco.

true story.
name: SUPER-HERO SPECIAL!

description:
SCI-FI Special!

Not so long ago, in our own galaxy really close...PATRICK The WOLF BOY Returns for some Sci-Fi-Fun! Watch what happens when Patrick's Dad takes him to see the new Movie! How long must they wait in line! And, what's going on with all those alien cos-players? They may be too much for Patrick to handle. The Force seems to be very strong with this youngling! AW YEAH! You may never look at mashed potatoes the same again. Join us for the universal wonderment beyond the stars as only Patrick the Wolf Boy can bring. Guest starring Zyggie the alien Patrick.

By Art Baltazar and Franco.
name: SCI-FI Special!

description:
Another Halloween Special

PATRICK is back for another Halloween! Its time for the school play and it looks like its bad luck for the one who plays the role of the squirrel! Do you ever wonder what its like to be a ghost? So does Patrick! But I don't think his mom will approve. Find out what happens at the Wax Museum with dad! Suddenly, the Screaming Pajama Lady is in for a Trick, or is it a Treat? Find out in this next exciting episode! AW YEAH! By Art Baltazar and Franco!
name: Another Halloween Special

description:
Wedding Special!

Love is in the air and Patrick the Wolf Boy's family just got invited to a wedding! What could possibly go wrong? Well, if our little "Ring Bearer" does his job correctly, everything should be okay....WAIT! PATRICK GET DOWN FROM THERE! WHO BROUGHT THE SQUIRREL? Oh no. Looks like we spoke too soon. Wedding Nuptial Hi-jinks Ensue. By Art Baltazar and Franco! Love the one you're with.
name: Wedding Special!

description:
After School Special

Welcome to School! Well, Welcome to After School! All seems dandy until....yep, you guessed...The BULLY is in town and he wants your lunch money! What's a Wolf Boy to do? Oh, we can guarantee Patrick will take care of this Bully his own way. And if we have any predictions, you can be sure that the squirrel is involved somehow! AW YEAH! By Art Baltazar and Franco with special backup story by Bob Renzas.
name: After School Special

description:
This Year's Halloween Special!

This Year's Halloween Special! YES! It's that time of year once again! Time for tricks and time for treats! You can learn a lot about witches from watching your neighbor...just ask Patrick! He might agree with you! But please make sure you have your facts correct before you decide to dump a bucket of water on her! PLUS! Do pumpkins hold the secret to this holiday? They are fascinating things indeed. Especially if you wear them on your head! Aw Yeah Jack-O-Lanterns! Join us for Wolf Boy fun! From the Eisner Winning creators Art Baltazar and Franco! Comics are awesome. Thanks.
name: This Year's Halloween Special!

description:
ROCK-N-ROLL Special!

The ROCK-N-ROLL Special! Yep. Summer is upon us. And the outdoor concert season is in full swing! Patrick's parents are about to get their funky groove on ... when suddenly, Patrick decides he wants to join the band! WHAT?! They find out quickly that an outdoor concert may too dangerous if you're the drummer in a rock band! Nothing a little face-paint can't handle. Special appearances by OOKLA the MOK, Poop House Reilly, and Kato the House Boy with HARE and Ozzie. By Art Baltazar and Franco!
name: ROCK-N-ROLL Special!

description:
Father's Day Special!

HAPPY Father's DAY! Are you ready? It's that same old question? What color tie do we get dad this year? Does he like the stripes? Maybe polka dots? In Patrick's case, maybe dad is into fur? Or even chewed up...something? There is no predicting what a little Wolf Boy will surprise you with next! But Patrick is not the only one with surprises. We present to you... Baby Squatch! That's right! His first appearance is in this issue! HA! You though you can get away from us didn't ya? Happy Father's Day, Dads. I think this one will make you laugh. By Art Baltazar and Franco.
name: Father's Day Special!

description:
HAPPY BIRTHDAY SPECIAL!

Happy Birthday Special! AW YEAH! Its Patrick's Birthday and there's a party! Make a Wish, Patrick! Don't eat the candles! What's a wolf boy to do when the love of his life thinks she just turned into...A WEREWOLF?! Patrick does what he does best! Uses his INSTINCT! That's right, That Wolf Boy instinct that HOWLS at the moon! ALSO! Just when you thought you've seen the last of those ZYGGIE ALIENS...guess what? YEP! They return too! Celebrate with us! You know you want to. By Art Baltazar and Franco!
name: Happy Birthday Special!

description:
AW YEAH NEW PATRICK STUFF!

AW YEAH NEW STUFF! The first comic collection of the new Devil's Due Trade-paperback now in digital comic form! AW YEAH! We had enough Patrick Comics to make it a 20 issue run! This issue is an event for sure! Patrick goes to a comic convention, then he goes to the vet, then he has a sleepover with the girls, he makes pancakes, terrorizes a clown, and even Patrick's Grandpa makes an appearance. See? Lots of stuff. Oh, and don't forget...The DDP GUY. By Art Baltazar and Franco.
name: AW YEAH NEW PATRICK STUFF!

description:
PATRICK'S DUE!

PATRICK'S DUE! Continuing the "never before" collection of the bonus DDP Patrick comic strips! This one will amaze! Carnival rides shouldn't be this scary. And neither should classroom "Show-N-Tells". And, what's a wolf boy to do for a piece of bubble gum around here? We should worry about the squirrel, I think. GUM! By Art Baltazar and Franco. True Story.
name: PATRICK'S DUE!

description:
AW YEAH PATRICK!

AW YEAH PATRICK! The tradition continues! The Wolf Boy and some Demons make a positive connection. I feel really sorry for that barber trying to give Patrick his first haircut. Hhmmm... let's see, that school Bathroom break may take longer than we think. What are they doing over there anyway? While during the Neighborhood Follies, The Pajama Lady can't catch a break. Water in the face again! Well, at least the DDP GUY is wearing clothes this time. Man, this is a weird one. Weird but awesome, y'know? By Art Baltazar and Franco. With Special Guest writers, Jamie Cosley and Rose Baltazar!
name: AW YEAH PATRICK!

description:
The Super Fantastic Patrick Color Special!

PATRICK in COLOR! Finally! After years in the making! The little wolf boy we all know and love....is presented here in full blazing COLOR! Maybe this is the start of some awesome? I truly believe so! The colorful masterpiece that brings Patrick The Wolf Boy into the modern age of AW YEAH COMICS! By Art Baltazar and Franco! (you probably already knew that) AW YEAH!
name: The Super Fantastic Patrick Color Special!

description: The coolest kids at Bayside High start their freshman year in this hilarious modern update of the smash-hit teen sitcom! This extra-sized book is loaded to The Max with two semesters... er, volumes of high school hijinks and the sold-out Bayside Warriors one-shot. Zack Morris, come out to plaaay!

description:
The Queen Of Death

Abelinda the witch awakens in a nightmarish world of entities seeking either to drive her mad or entrap her there eternally. She is joined by two unlikely companions whose motivations remain ambivalent for the time being. Journey with Abelinda as she delves deeper into her family's occult history and learns more about her mystical abilities.

Alice in Wonderland

Alex Cooper falls into the dream world of Comatose, a world that is part dream, part game; full of action, adventure, and blood thirsty monsters. With the help of his friend Kevin he begins to make his escape from this world, but they soon discover that there is more to this world than meets the eye. Follow Kevin and Alex and their adventures in Comatose.

Chapter 5: Alice in Wonderland

Alex returns to his normal life, but finds himself unable to shake his dream of Comatose.

description: With his family safe (for now), Chavo must uncover the source of his 'Hunter's Rage,' the newfound superpower coursing through his veins, before the evil Junta del Jaguar can regroup from the shadows. A new breed of superhero is born as legendary pro wrestler Chavo Guerrero stars in his first comic book adventure!

volume.name: El Credo del Guerrero de Chavo Guerrero

description:
Goddesses Part 3: Crones

Zia returns to America in Empress #7, and blood spills!

While police officers investigate a gory mess left behind on an abandoned ship, the producer of Silver Screen Studios waits for information on his missing actress, Zia. What he gets is more than he could have ever imagined!

Another tragic flashback to the past reveals more of Zia's ancestral origins, and gremlins of the subterranean deity continue to feast in Goddesses, Chapter III: Crones!
name: Goddesses Part 3: Crones

description: A full-length detective story, starring Pam the javelina. A javelina looks like a pig, but it is not a pig. It's a hooded peccary. This one smokes, cracks jokes and investigates crime in Falling Rock National Park.

Paranoia Strikes Deep

Kevin Keene is given the role of a lifetime: infiltrate the Cohort of Christ. Meanwhile, the Kazoops, Betty Pierce, and Sean Sullivan plot their next move.
name: Paranoia Strikes Deep

description:
Breakdown

The fourth riveting issue of the 8 part sci-fi graphic novel!

Part hard-boiled mystery, part sci-fi manga, and all out-of-this-world adventure

Things are not going well for Z. Bounty Hunters are after him, the law is hunting him, and someone named Luthor Turaxus is behind it all. What he doesn't need now is to be stuck on some far off planet. But that's just what is about to happen. Luckily, he's also about to find out why this is all going down.

Echoes

Five Years after the attack of the Dragons, we find Astor travelling far from home, now a hunted fugitive with only three friends to look out for him. While he tries to adapt to his new reality, the people that track him draw close to his location.
name: Echoes

description: 13 mechanically enhanced tales by Sue Olcott, Matt Feazell & Jim Mackey, Kel Crum, Steven Myers, Kate E. Lore, Michael A. Carroll, Alu-Marr, Steve Peters, Troy Vevasis, Aleksandar Jovic, Dale Martin, Canada Keck, Pam Bliss, Brent Richardson and Bob Corby.

description: The story of Paragon continues. Who are 'the Tenth' and what do they want from our hero!

Legacy

An all new story begins as Liza is training Markie to use her powers while Gail adjusts to school life after skipping two grades. The Desert Fox drops a bomb and nothing will be the same again. Also? NOW IN FULL COLOR!
name: Legacy

description:
Join the Fight Part 1

Pro athletes Isaac Chike, Douglass Larter, Gerard Rioux, Danielle Peters, and Miguel Monteiro enter a much more dangerous game as they learn a greater destiny awaits them. Will they become Protectors, and defend mankind from an alien menace bent on enslaving the Earth?
name: Join the Fight Part 1

description:
Chapter 20 part 2

Danny confronts Seth on a heartbroken Trish's behalf.
name: Chapter 20 Part 2

description:
How Could This Be?

With the Great Seal now in the hands of the Kalizarians, time begins to run out for the entire realm. Silvermain is wounded thanks to a hapless scout and Raulph tries to put together his own plan concerning Prince Christian. Yet in the midst of chaos life springs anew as Pandora makes the final choice to keep the child saved from the burning inn. But will an extremely hesitant Ravenwood still be by her side?
name: How Could This Be?

description:
Imperium: Part 6

As the first arc comes to a close, Alina finds new allies in the Wastelands and Zarran submits to the judgement of the land. Meanwhile, Emperor Trovaar's health remains in question as he learns of Doctor Murrell's deception.
name: Imperium: Part 6

description:
Follow the Glowing Ghost

Rowen learns the reason his new home is called the "haunted" tower as two unusual ghosts take him on a short tour of the fifth floor and lead him to information that could help him in his quest.

Now if only he can convince his demon landlady to take it easy on him after trespassing into an enchanted library on the forbidden floor of the tower...
name: Follow the Glowing Ghost

description: In a most brutal and gory battle 700 Knights of St. John defended Europe from a massive Ottoman Empire invasion force, in 1565.

Riddles and Shrooms

Deep in the heart of Dark Leaf Forest, lies a musty little inn called the Silver Dagger. An abandoned dishwasher, named Bean, must navigate his way through cranky ogres, mysterious trolls, and responsibility of saving his world.
name: Riddles and Shrooms

Eye of Ra

1948: Abaris, joined by a pair of Golem, Ushabtis of the Pharoh, Merene, pursue the Mummy Queen, Nitocris, to a Manhattan power station where something strange is afoot.
name: Eye of Ra

description:
Legacy

Jonathin Quackup flees with his family from an evil warlord and faces his destiny.
name: Legacy

volume.name: Jonathin Quackup of the Planet Weralt

description: After witnessing the death of an old school friend, Gideon Black gets drawn into a murder mystery and the machinations of Maximilian and The FAB!

Mr Button's: One Shot, is a very different Teddy Bear Tale. This is what happens when one Teddy Bear decides to go 'Punisher' on the Boogeyman and his Monsters under the Bed, and brings the pain.

This isn't your typical cuddly defender tale as we journey into the realm of the Underbed with Mr Button, a particularly psychotic little Teddy Bear with a love of really big guns and explosives!

The Hidden World Part 1

OBSKURA is a science fiction adventure within the frame of Ancient Aliens meets Fringe. It parts from the premise that all mythological tales, the paranormal, and unexplained phenomena we have recorded through the years are not only real, but they all come together to secretly shape humanity. It will share light on the origin of creatures found in our myths and legends while establishing the origins of life on Earth through the eyes of the main character.
name: The Hidden World Part 1

description:
Part 1: Infiltration

Lánhuā Wen, codename Orchid, works for the A.D.S. and not only is she the top ranked infiltrator of the organisation, she is also their best female melee fighter, a cunning tactician and has a degree in psychology. And she is supposed to be on vacation.
name: Part 1: Infiltration

description: Trina Robbins has spent the last thirty years recording the accomplishments of a century of women cartoonists, and Pretty in Ink is her ultimate book, a revised, updated and rewritten history of women cartoonists, with more color illustrations than ever before, and with some startling new discoveries (such as a Native American woman cartoonist from the 1940s who was also a Corporal in the women’s army, and the revelation that a cartoonist included in all of Robbins’s previous histories was a man!) In the pages of Pretty in Ink you’ll find new photos and correspondence from cartoonists Ethel Hays and Edwina Dumm, and the true story of Golden Age comic book star Lily Renee, as intriguing as the comics she drew. Although the comics profession was dominated by men, there were far more women working in the profession throughout the 20th century than other histories indicate, and they have flourished in the 21st. Robbins not only documents the increasing relevance of women throughout the 20th century, with mainstream creators such as Ramona Fradon and Dale Messick and alternative cartoonists such as Lynda Barry, Carol Tyler, and Phoebe Gloeckner, but the latest generation of women cartoonists―Megan Kelso, Cathy Malkasian, Linda Medley, and Lilli Carré, among many others. Robbins is the preeminent historian of women comic artists; forget her previous histories: Pretty in Ink is her most comprehensive volume to date.
name: SC

volume.name: Pretty in Ink: North American Women Cartoonists 1896–2010

description:
The Awakening

When Ephraim Balogun finds himself caught up in an explosion that rocks nearby Malta City, little did he know he was being chosen and will be whisked away into an embroiled conflict between gods and men. In a world trying to deal with the sudden appearance of costumed vigilantes and super humans, Ephraim must join hands with other heroes; business man, Captain-J , Police officer, Agent Blue Fox and street racer, Afropilot, awakening to threatening evil supernatural anomalies before they end the world.
name: The Awakening

description:
Welcome to A-Time, not another dimension, not a parallel world, but your very own neighborhood bereft of linear time! Here, past, present and future merge like expressway off-ramps. Here, bestial six legged Quirks can alter the future, Glitches of powerful emotion swarm once-stable lives, and Archetypes leave (big) footprints. After a nervous breakdown, genius double-doctorate Harry Keller wasn’t looking for A-Time, but he found it. Like many explorers before him, he soon learns that the terra incognita is dazzling and dangerous, because whatever happens in A-Time also has an effect here, from benign to devastating. And, just like those explorers, Harry Keller thinks he’s the first. Being wrong, of course, he stumbles onto a devious plan to have Ronald Reagan re-elected president, so he can die in office and fulfill the Zero Curse! And yes, in context, it makes total sense! Can Harry set things right before he’s locked away for keeps? *Here, collected in a single volume for the first time is best-selling author Stefan Petrucha’s 1989 comic book debut, with art by the late, great Tom Sutton, at his quirky best, psychedelic colors by Paul Mounts and eye-popping covers by Jeffrey K. Potter, known for his work for Analog and Asimov’s Science Fiction magazines. Collects issues 1-4.

Note: The digital edition (11/16/2016) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: TPB

description:
'Whatever happened to The Archetype?' is a four part superhero/ sci-fi 'epic' that tries to answer the question - What happens when caped avengers get old and everyone thinks that their superhero persona was either a myth, or worse still the ramblings of a crazy old man?

At the Cherry Blossom Residential Home for the elderly, long-time resident Christopher Quin tells his life story to a mystery visitor and attempts to convince him of his alien heritage, his past life as a superhero, and his relationship with 1940's supervillain Frenzy.

The Light of Knowledge Reveals the Horrors of the Unknown Driven by uncertainty, the Mars expedition reaches its destination. Bristow, Dunwood and crew travel to the barren surface, and find a truth more frightening than they ever imagined. Can Captain Bristow once again complete his mission? And if so, at what cost?

Note: The digital edition (7/13/2016) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Chapter 5: The Light of Knowledge Reveals the Horrors of the Unknown

description:
The Zero Dimension

Introducing Aden the Grey alien, enslaved in The Zero Dimension, forced to mine for ore in extremely perilous circumstances, Aden snaps and makes a heroic freedom run.

Mega-Child and Robert Finch discuss the unfolding plot to conquer Superion, a gigantic Cyberopolis with an onslaught of F-10 Jet fighters and Merciless Ambush Predators.

Cyber Puff has a cryptic foretelling of war for Lurkdarker, who is still spying on his Lady Sweet, Lisa Warren, as she deals with her disappointment and crippling boredom and loneliness, hanging out with her new pet Hug Monkey. Except her Hug Monkey is different than the other Hug Monkeys, as it evolves into super-intelligence rapidly, naming itself Eurasmus, mispronouncing the authors name of the book he is reading: "Praise of Folly".
name: The Zero Dimension

description:
The Cruel Dance Music of the Universe -Part 5

Conclusion? Bob seeks help in destroying the 'Dream Machine' that created the 3-eyed purple monkeys... But, Can anyone help him? Is anyone willing? His Mother is living with a psychopath... His father is powerless... Can things get any worse?

description: Boris and Richard are friends. A friendly Reptilian wants to be friends too. Is this a good idea? Or is it a shared hallucination?

description:
Deirdre yearns to be wanted... until she is. Sought by a mysterious force, Deirdre finds she may not be as alone as she thought.

Experience exciting locations and fantastical creatures: unfamiliar technology and unfamiliar customs. Join Deirdre on her quest to find her family, on her journey home.

The story continues! Nexus' new friend, the Larp, recounts his story of banishment by Gourmando to this strange dimension full of mists and monsters.

The Nexus Newspaper strip is made in the tradition of the classic newspaper strips and at classic newspaper strip size of 17" x 22"! You have to see these in person to truly appreciate them!

Included here is Nexus Comic Strips #16-21 plus pages from "When She was Young", a fully painted story fearing Sundra Peale in her college days that was originally published in Nexus 100. Extras include Steve Rude's original designs for Gourmando and Gnosis and the strip "Out There" by Bill Wiist!

E.G.H.I.K. - Part I

Subject K and Colt do some recon, while the Pale Man is busy trying to find another source for Doctor Vernon's research. Doc Layne and Leo try to help Spez.

Join the Fight Part 2

Revelations abound as football star Isaac Chike must decide if the homeless man he meets is a madman, or something much more. Meanwhile, the forces of evil align against those who will become the Protectors.

description:
Lose

The survival of the new community in the city stands on the brink as those who resent life outside the gloom conspire with the Veratu to tear it all down. Raina tries to put her struggles behind her, Donna finally understands the power driving this world, and her father tries to rediscover what really matters to him, but all are unaware of the chaos and devastation about to hit. Pandemonium! Panic! Some will live, some will die, and everything will change as the curtain falls.
name: Lose
